a_0.formal problem:
theorem
fixes f g :: "real \<Rightarrow> real"
assumes h0 : "\<forall> x. f x = g (g x) - g x"
and h1 : "\<forall> x. g x = 2 * x - 1"
shows  "f 3 = 4"
a_0.formal solution:
(* ### Problem
 If $f(x)=g(g(x))-g(x)$ and $g(x)=2x-1$, find $f(3)$. The final Answer is 4
 ### Proof
 We have $f(3) = g(g(3)) - g(3)$. Since $g(3) = 2(3) - 1 = 5$, we have $f(3) = g(g(3)) - g(3) = g(5) - 5 = 2(5)-1-5 = \boxed{4}$.
 *)

fixes f g :: "real \<Rightarrow> real"
